A dying two-year-old's last Christmas wish has come true as her community worked together to transform her house into a winter wonderland.

Calianna Griggs's family wanted to stage an early Christmas for the toddler, who may not make it to December.

She was diagnosed with Li-Fraumeni Syndrome and adrenocortical carcinoma in April and despite chemotherapy and multiple surgeries, doctors say she has just a month to live.

But on Thursday, thanks to dozens of volunteers and donations from the community - Cali got her dying wish.

