But Mr Griggs added that it is unlikely she will live out the full three months: 'We want her last Christmas to be the best and we also want for her funeral service to be very special.'

Mr Griggswas tearful as he told MailOnline: 'She is in a world of pain that I couldn't even imagine.

'It is just getting harder and harder and harder.'

The couple noticed something was wrong when Cali ballooned from aged two clothes to aged five clothes in just 10 days.

She is now continuing to swell up and is becoming increasingly lethargic. 

In a recent local TV interview, Mr Griggs broke down in tears as he could hear the microphone picking up Cali struggling to breathe.

'It was just too much. She finds it so difficult. Sometimes now she just sleeps for hours at a time.' 

